aims-os-math (2.0) trixie; urgency=medium

  * v2.0 — rebase to Debian 13 Trixie.
    + Drop sagemath + sagemath-doc from Depends. SageMath is currently
      not in Trixie because its 9.5-6 upload requires python3 < 3.12
      while Trixie ships python3 3.13 (Debian RC bug tracker:
      https://tracker.debian.org/pkg/sagemath). The install-on-demand
      path via `mamba install -c conda-forge sagemath` is now the
      recommended way — Miniforge already ships in aims-os-core.
    + Everything else (NumPy, SciPy, pandas, matplotlib, sympy,
      sklearn, statsmodels, networkx, JupyterLab back-end, Maxima,
      wxMaxima, Octave + scientific modules, R + tidyverse, TeX Live
      with French / English, TeXstudio + biber, GeoGebra, gnuplot,
      gdb / valgrind, OpenBLAS / LAPACK / FFTW / HDF5 / GMP / MPFR
      headers) is present in Trixie with the same package names.

 -- AIMS Senegal IT <hakim@aims-senegal.org>  Thu, 21 May 2026 00:00:00 +0000

aims-os-math (1.0) bookworm; urgency=medium

  * Initial release.
    + Pulls the AIMS OS scientific computing stack: Python SciPy
      ecosystem (numpy, scipy, pandas, matplotlib, sympy, sklearn,
      statsmodels, networkx), JupyterLab + ipywidgets, SageMath with
      fr/en docs, Maxima/wxMaxima, GNU Octave plus the scientific
      add-on modules, R with the tidyverse and rmarkdown, full TeX
      Live with French and English language packs, TeXstudio and
      biber, GeoGebra and gnuplot, gdb / valgrind and the
      OpenBLAS / LAPACK / FFTW / HDF5 / GMP / MPFR development
      headers for numerical software.

 -- AIMS Senegal IT <hakim@aims-senegal.org>  Tue, 19 May 2026 12:00:00 +0000
